### Discussed in https://github.com/keystonejs/keystone/discussions/8874

<div type='discussions-op-text'>

<sup>Originally posted by **rivaslive** October 25, 2023</sup>
I'm trying to use **`startAuthedSession`** for a firebase login for my clients (Not admin UI) but I can't find how to create a token with the user


my code is this

```typescript
 mergeSchemas({
    schemas: [schema],
    typeDefs: `
      type Mutation {
        authenticateUserWithFirebase(token: String!): UserAuthenticationWithPasswordResult
      `,
    resolvers: {
      Mutation: {
        async authenticateUserWithFirebase(
          root,
          { token: verifyToken }: { token: string },
          context: KeystoneContext
        ) {
          const firebaseToken = await firebaseApp
            .auth()
            .verifyIdToken(verifyToken);
          const { uid } = firebaseToken;

          try {
            const users = await context.query.User.findMany({
              where: { firebaseUID: uid },
              query: SESSION_DATA_FRAGMENT
            });

            if (!users || !users?.length) {
              console.error(`Unable to find user-authenticate`);
              throw new Error('User not found');
            }

            const item = users[0];
            const token = await context.startAuthedSession({
              item,
              list: { key: 'User' }
            });
            return { item, token };
          } catch (error) {
            throw error;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  });

```

The puntual error is

```typescript
const token = await context.startAuthedSession({
    item,
    list: { key: 'User' }
});
```

Could you help me create a token in v6?</div>

