for whoever needs it in the future, this working:

```typescript
const context = keystoneContext.sudo();

// Update system state
const sessionToken = await context?.sessionStrategy?.start({
    data: {
        listKey: 'User',
        itemId: userDb.id
     },
     context
});

// return Failure if sessionStrategy.start() returns null
if (typeof sessionToken !== 'string' || sessionToken.length === 0) {
    return { code: 'FAILURE', message: 'Failed to start session.' };
}
```

Code example here [getBaseAuthSchema.ts](https://github.com/keystonejs/keystone/blob/main/packages/auth/src/gql/getBaseAuthSchema.ts)

