I am in the process of seeding data and using the syntax specified in the docs for the `createOne` method of the DB API  throws an error
Here is what my code looks like
```ts
await keystoneContext.db.Product.createOne({
    data: {
        ...product,
        photo: { create: [{ altText: product.description }] },
    },
})
```
Error ```GraphQLError: Field "0" is not defined by type "<certain type generated in the graphql schema>"```

but this 👇🏽 fixes it
```ts
// ........
        photo: { create: { altText: product.description } },
// ..........
```

